	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I know alot of you don't agree with MQing. . .I'm a Iksar and yes I did find ways around KOS.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the red sash I ran into FP invis pulled Ran'un away along w/ the guildmasters I FDed in the big sand area then i killed him after the guildmasters left. Yes I did start to quest the sashes on a mule but after I heard they drop I droped him. As for the headband I bought my orange headband and bought all the rest of the heads and what not.  I just kept questing the white sash on the mule for the faction.  I  MQed e code, the idol, and the pipes.   Yes i know this sounds lazy to you but hear me out LOL.  Not only is it hard for Ikasrs but I'm on a PvP server and thus PvP gets in the way not some of the time ALL THE TIME.  And in addition everyone is always after the darky.  So lets see how well you try to camp Targin the Rock when you got 4 gnomes pecking at your feet.  Same with Raster. . .not a lot of ppl try to camp raster that I know of but when monks come to raster camp trust me they are ready to fight for it.  Just to let all you blubies know on PvP servers you try to get things done quick and fast because the more time you spend standing in one place the more likely you are to be PKed.  And I for one am a pureist that means there is no Xteaming for me.  Xteamer-One who groups/guilded with a person of another team. But yes I do not feel to comfortable MQing all this I have spent time at all the camps spending many hours tryin to camp them and when someone sends you a tell outta no where asking if I want to buy this MQ I said YES.  Hate me if you want but you don't have your epic :P and I do.<br>[52 Disciple]Xotron(Iksar)&lt;Trao`lech&gt;<br>Vallon Zek<br>LONG LIVE PUREIST<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
